                <div class="jonra" data-uuid="a3cb6f6074934d4b9726e626a9040d6d">
                    <h2 data-uuid="d726b9764a434c86b20a33019abcfee2">Navajo Code Talkers</h2>
                    <p class="source" data-uuid="237abe6c2ffe428e945d279e582beda5">The Japanese could not easily crack Allied codes. Specially trained Navajo recruits relayed messages using the unique Navajo language. In some cases, military words were not part of the Navajo language, so the code talk used replacement words. For example, <i>war chief</i> was used to indicate <i>commanding general</i> and <i>iron fish </i>meant <i>submarine</i>.</p>
                </div>
